         <abstract>
            <p>Certain polynomials invariant under a permutation group $G$ (so called $G$-polynomials) play an important role in several computational methods of Galois theory. Since their practical value depends on the degree, it is important to know $G$-polynomials of smallest possible degree. A reasonable technique to find such $G$-polynomials is presented, and for certain classes of groups an explicit description is obtained. The list of $G$-polynomials given by Stauduhar in vol. 27 of this journal is thereby enlarged and improved. As an application of $G$-polynomials, three important resolvents of quintic and sextic algebraic equations are computed and a parametric family of sextic equations with given Galois group is exhibited.</p>
          </abstract>
